Author:
Vol / Page:  III/16
Edition:
Quote:  As roads became better, motor transport could be used in back-block areas, and more and more of the smaller post offices could be closed and the settlers given rural delivery service which brought the post office to their front gate. <i>Ibid.</i> 17. With the introduction of rural deliveries many country post offices were closed and the number is now [<i>sc.</i> 1955] a thousand less than at its peak of 2,042 offices in 1915.
