Quote:  For some years the Wellington-Picton ferry steamer used to call at several of the Bays in Queen Charlotte Sound and to drop the mail. On December 8, 1911, a general survey was made of the service, which at the time was known as the "Rural Delivery Marlborough Sounds", and it was decided not to disturb the arrangements which then existed for the delivery of the mail by ferry.
